and two had stent revisions. In the other patients, stents became occluded after 
3-55 months. The reason for stent occlusion was a stone in one patient; in the 
others, the causes were not proved.
CONCLUSION: Results of stent placement for treatment of benign biliary 
strictures are not encouraging. However, the patient population is too limited 
to allow final conclusions.

