(1)Cattedra di Chirurgia Vascolare, UniversitÃ  di Roma Tor Vergata.

This retrospective study was carried out from January, 1990, to September, 1994, 
after reviewing a series of 100 patients submitted to 143 percutaneous maneuvers 
(PTA) for aortoiliac revascularization (PTA, PTA and stenting, PTA and bypass). 
This study was aimed at conforming as much as possible our patients selection 
